```ad-note
Platinum is used due to it allows close contact of hydrogen gas and hydrogen ions, so that the equilibrium is formed quickly. Platinum electrode is also inert and hence won't involved in the reaction.

Conditions for standard hydrogen electrode are:
	1. 1 atm gas pressure
	2. 1.00 mol dm^-3 concentration of H+ ions
	3. 298 K of temperature
	4. Pt(s) as catalyst

The half equation can be written as following: 
$H^{+} (aq) \ + \ e^{-} \ \rightleftharpoons \ \frac{1}{2}H_{2} (g) \qquad E^{\textordmasculine} = 0.00V$
